      • DEVICE_FLOW_USER_CODE_LENGTH

        static final String DEVICE_FLOW_USER_CODE_LENGTH
        The number of actual characters in a user code. E.g. if this is 6, then 6 characters will be created before it is divided up with the separator
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • DEVICE_FLOW_CODE_SEPARATOR

        static final String DEVICE_FLOW_CODE_SEPARATOR
        The character(s) to put between each period. So if
        1. raw code = ABC123
        2. separator = _
        3. period length = 3
        a user code of ABC_123 would be returned to the user.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • DEVICE_FLOW_CODE_PERIOD_LENGTH

        static final String DEVICE_FLOW_CODE_PERIOD_LENGTH
        The length of a period i.e., how many characters are together at once between separators. This is a small number like 3, 4 or maybe 5 so that the user can just look at it and read it off. If the user code were ABC123DEC456 then

        period = 3 ==> ABC_123_DEC_456

        period = 4 ==> ABC1_23DE_C456
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
